quran[25]{c,v,t}:
  25,53,"And it is He who let forth the two seas, this one Sweet, grateful to taste, and this salt, bitter to the tongue, and He set between them a barrier, and a ban forbidden"
  25,54,"And it is He who created of water a mortal, and made him kindred of blood and marriage; thy Lord is All-powerful"
  25,55,"And they serve, apart from God, what neither profits them nor hurts them; and the unbeliever is ever a partisan against his Lord"
  25,56,"We have sent thee not, except good tidings to bear, and warning"
  25,57,"Say: 'I do not ask of you a wage for this, except for him who wishes to take to his Lord a way"
  25,58,"Put thy trust in the Living God, the Undying, and proclaim His praise. Sufficiently is He aware of His servants sins"
  25,59,"who created the heavens and the earth, and what between them is, in six days, then sat Himself upon the Throne, the All-compassionate: ask any informed of Him"
  25,60,"But when they are told, 'Bow yourselves to the All-merciful,' they say, 'And what is the All-merciful? Shall we bow ourselves to what thou biddest us?' And it increases them in aversion"
  25,61,"Blessed be He who has set in heaven constellations, and has set among them a lamp, and an illuminating moon"
  25,62,And it is He who made the night and day a succession for whom He desires to remember or He desires to be thankful
  25,63,"The servants of the All-merciful are those who walk in the earth modestly and who, when the ignorant address them, say, 'Peace"
  25,64,who pass the night prostrate to their Lord and standing
  25,65,"who say, 'Our Lord, turn Thou from us the chastisement of Gehenna; surely its chastisement is torment most terrible"
  25,66,evil it is as a lodging-place and an abode
  25,67,"who, when they expend, are neither prodigal nor parsimonious, but between that is a just stand"
  25,68,"who call not upon another god with God, nor slay the soul God has forbidden except by right, neither fornicate, for whosoever does that shall meet the price"
  25,69,"of sin-doubled shall be the chastisement for him on the Resurrection Day, and he shall dwell therein humbled"
  25,70,"save him who repents, and believes, and does righteous work -- those, God will change their evil deeds into good deeds, for God is ever All-forgiving, All-compassionate"
  25,71,"and whosoever repents, and does righteousness, he truly turns to God in repentance"
  25,72,"And those who bear not false witness and, when they pass by idle talk, pass by with dignity"
  25,73,"who, when they are reminded of the signs of their Lord, fall not down thereat deaf and blind"
  25,74,"who say, 'Our Lord, give us refreshment of our wives and seed, and make us a model to the godfearing"
  25,75,"Those shall be recompensed with the highest heaven, for that they endured patiently, and they shall receive therein a greeting and --' Peace"
  25,76,Therein they shall dwell forever; fair it is as a lodging-place and an abode
  25,77,"Say: 'My Lord esteems you not at all were it not for your prayer, for you have cried lies, and it shall surely be fastened"